* Selenium Class 8

* Implicit Wait:
  - Will be applied for findElement method.

* Explicit Wait: (AKA WebDriver wait)
  - Is used to tell the web driver to wait for a certain condition
    before throwing an exception for a specified condition.

* Explicit Wait Works with:
  -  ExceptedCondition class & waits until
     certain conditions are met or given time is achieved.

- * sign in xpath is a wild card which can identify any tagname
- Syntax: //*[contains(text(), 'Welcome')]

* Fluent Wait: (AKA Global wait means complete script)
  - Is used to tell web driver to wait for certain condition
    As well as its frequency before throwing an exception.

**** Long Story short ****
- Implicit wait = Waits to locate the element.
- Explicit wait = Waits until certain condition
- Fluent Wait   = Sets timeouts, polling & ignores needed exceptions.

* WebTables:
  - Are elements on the webpage, Which are constructed by having rows & columns.

* Types of WebTables:
  1. Static WebTable = Data is fixed/nothing changes
  2. Dynamic WebTable = Data is not fixed/changes

* WebTables Consist of different sections or parts:
<table>
     <thread>
              <tr> -- row
                  <th></th> -- column data or heading
              </tr>
     </thread>
     <tbody>
              <tr> -- row
                  <td></td> -- table data
              </tr> --
     </tbody>
</table>